Introduction
2144 001 205 0312, referred to as “Harper'' by the Traditionalists and “Tomato” by the Revolutionists. Harper has been working as a secretary for Roger since he was elected President. Harper is a Revolutionist spy working for the Traditionalists. She relays information back to her Revolutionist allies. Harper’s parents are respectable members in society and extremely wealthy. Her personality is carefree and playful and at a very young age she noticed how unfair The Traditionalists and Roger were.

After meeting Bean, Harper grew closer to the Revolutionists and was attracted to their principles. Though they did not trust her initially because of her background, as the Revolutionists got to know Harper they could see her heart was in the right place and she shared the revolutionist vision. Harper became a full fledged member of the Revolutionists and was given the name “Tomato.”

Appearance
The name “Tomato” was chosen as a homage to her short red hair. The ends of her hair are dyed a pale yellow and sit just below her chin in length. Her nose and cheeks house a number of freckles and she calls it her most charming feature. She has a nose ring and wears different kinds of abstract earrings depending on her mood.
Although she is required to wear business attire at work, she prefers a casual and comfortable look. She is often seen with large sweaters, overalls, boots, and her signature black scarf.

Personality
In short, Harper has a heart of gold. From a young age, Harper could tell the Traditionalists were selfish and ignorant. She hated the way her parents and other members of her class treated those of a lower class. Harper has always wanted to create change but had no ability to. Her parents made sure to limit her contact with those of other classes. Her personality did not align with that of the upper class children she was around and it was only until she met the Revolutionists that she was able to be her true self.
